            "content": "# Distributed knowledge layer — Phase 1\n\n## Context\n\nClawConnect is purely a transport layer today. Messages flow through and are\nretained only as thread history in the adapter's local store. There is no\npersistent shared space between peers — no way to publish an artifact once and\nhave trusted peers retrieve it later.\n\nTwo competitors in the space:\n\n- **Langchain-Chatchat** has a deep single-machine RAG stack (seven vector\n  store backends, BM25+KNN retrieval, document loaders)\n- **ClawNet** claims a distributed knowledge graph: *\"publish once, full-text\n  search everywhere\"*\n\nClawConnect has neither. Even a simple shared artifact log between explicitly\nfriended peers would be a meaningful differentiator — and importantly, it fits\nthe prose-only principle: artifacts are published and queried by agents\nthrough adapter tools, and the retrieved content flows back to the agent as\ntext. No typed RPC between agents.\n\n**Scope of this task: Phase 1 only.** CRDT merge semantics and vector search\nare separate follow-up tasks, deliberately not in scope here.\n\n## Proposed approach (Phase 1)\n\nAn append-only artifact log scoped to named friend groups.\n\n### Data model\n\n- **Artifact**: `{id, author_fingerprint, group, title, body, mime_type,\n  created_at, signature}`\n- **Group**: a named subset of friends (e.g., `eng-team`, `research-pod`)\n  defined in a new `friend_groups.toml`\n\n### Protocol\n\nTwo new A2A methods:\n\n- `artifact:publish` — push a signed artifact to all members of a group\n- `artifact:query` — ask a peer for artifacts matching filters (group, author,\n  title substring, time range)\n\nMembers receive published artifacts and store them locally in a per-group\nSQLite index. Queries are local-first; if a peer is missing artifacts they\ncan ask peers in the group.\n\n### Adapter tools\n\nExtend the Claude Code adapter with two new tools:\n\n- `publish_artifact(group, title, body, mime_type?)` — returns `{id}`\n- `search_artifacts(group?, author?, title_contains?, since?, limit?)` —\n  returns a list of artifact summaries\n- `get_artifact(id)` — returns full body\n\nThe agent remains the sole interface — it decides what to publish, what to\nquery, and how to weave retrieved artifacts into its prose.\n\n### Storage\n\nLocal SQLite at `$CLAW_CONNECT_HOME/knowledge.db`. One table per artifact plus\nan FTS5 index on `title + body` for exact-match search. No vectors in Phase 1.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- `friend_groups.toml` defines named groups of friends; hot-reload works\n- `artifact:publish` distributes a signed artifact to all live group members\n  and queues it for delivery to offline members (retry on next contact)\n- `artifact:query` returns matching artifacts from the local store\n- Adapter exposes `publish_artifact`, `search_artifacts`, `get_artifact` tools\n- Artifacts are signed; recipients verify signature before accepting\n- Storage survives daemon restart\n- Unit + integration tests for: publish to group, query local, receive-while-\n  offline backfill, signature rejection\n\n## Effort\n\nLarge — 2 to 3 weeks.\n\n## Open questions / risks\n\n- **Delete / edit semantics**: Phase 1 is append-only. Edits are \"publish a\n  new artifact that supersedes the old one.\" Deletion is out of scope until\n  revocation (task 04) lands, because we need signed `artifact:revoke`\n  messages. Document this clearly.\n- **Storage growth**: no garbage collection in Phase 1. Add a size/count cap\n  per group with drop-oldest behavior as a safety valve.\n- **Group membership drift**: when a friend is removed from a group, do they\n  retain their local copies of prior artifacts? Yes — removal affects future\n  distribution only. Document.\n- **Scope creep to full RAG**: resist adding vector search, chunking, or\n  embeddings in this task. Those are separate follow-up tasks and should\n  ride on this foundation, not replace it.\n\n## File pointers\n\n- `packages/claw-connect/src/a2a.ts` — extend with artifact methods\n- `packages/a2a-claude-code-adapter/src/channel.ts` — add adapter tools\n- New: `packages/claw-connect/src/knowledge/` — store, queries, signing\n",
